### API Rate Limiting & Analytics Dashboard - HTTP Requests Collection
# This file can be run directly using the VS Code REST Client extension.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000
@email = tester_{{$timestamp}}@example.com
@password = Password123!

### 1. Signup New User
# @name signup
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Limiter Tester",
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### 2. Login User (to get accessToken)
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### Get Access Token from Login Response
@authToken = {{login.response.body.accessToken}}

### 3. Create Project A (Standard Rate Limit: 5 requests per minute)
# @name createProjectA
POST {{baseUrl}}/projects
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Standard Rate Limit Project",
  "targetBaseUrl": "https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com",
  "rateLimit": {
    "windowMs": 60000,
    "maxRequests": 5
  }
}

### Get API Key for Project A
@apiKeyA = {{createProjectA.response.body.apiKey}}

### 4. Create Project B (Fast Testing Rate Limit: 5 requests per 10 seconds)
# @name createProjectB
POST {{baseUrl}}/projects
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Fast Test Project",
  "targetBaseUrl": "https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com",
  "rateLimit": {
    "windowMs": 10000,
    "maxRequests": 5
  }
}

### Get API Key for Project B
@apiKeyB = {{createProjectB.response.body.apiKey}}

### =========================================================================
### PROXY & RATE LIMITING TEST SUITE
### =========================================================================

### Test Request 1: Call Proxy (Project B - Expect 200, check rate limit headers)
GET {{baseUrl}}/proxy/{{apiKeyB}}/posts/1

### Test Request 2: Call Proxy (Project B - Expect 200, remaining count decreases)
GET {{baseUrl}}/proxy/{{apiKeyB}}/posts/1

### Test Request 3: Call Proxy (Project B - Expect 200)
GET {{baseUrl}}/proxy/{{apiKeyB}}/posts/1

### Test Request 4: Call Proxy (Project B - Expect 200)
GET {{baseUrl}}/proxy/{{apiKeyB}}/posts/1

### Test Request 5: Call Proxy (Project B - Expect 200, remaining count is 0)
GET {{baseUrl}}/proxy/{{apiKeyB}}/posts/1

### Test Request 6: Call Proxy (Project B - Expect 429 Rate Limit Exceeded)
# Wait up to 10 seconds from Request 1 to see the window reset. If sent within
# 10 seconds of Request 1, this will return 429 status code with a JSON error.
GET {{baseUrl}}/proxy/{{apiKeyB}}/posts/1

### Test Request 7: Invalid API Key Bypass (Expect 404, no rate limit headers)
GET {{baseUrl}}/proxy/invalid_api_key_xyz_987/posts/1

### Test Request 8: Query Parameters Preservation
GET {{baseUrl}}/proxy/{{apiKeyB}}/comments?postId=1

### =========================================================================
### ANALYTICS API — PART 6
### =========================================================================
# First capture the project ID — run createProjectA above, then:
@projectId = {{createProjectA.response.body.id}}

### Analytics 1: Summary — last 24 hours (default range)
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}/analytics/summary
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Analytics 2: Summary — last 7 days
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}/analytics/summary?range=7d
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Analytics 3: Summary — last 30 days
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}/analytics/summary?range=30d
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Analytics 4: Summary — invalid range falls back to 24h (AC #9)
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}/analytics/summary?range=banana
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Analytics 5: Timeseries — hourly buckets for last 24h (gap-filled)
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}/analytics/timeseries?range=24h
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Analytics 6: Timeseries — daily buckets for last 7d
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}/analytics/timeseries?range=7d
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Analytics 7: Timeseries — daily buckets for last 30d
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}/analytics/timeseries?range=30d
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Analytics 8: Status Breakdown — 24h
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}/analytics/status-breakdown?range=24h
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Analytics 9: Status Breakdown — 7d
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}/analytics/status-breakdown?range=7d
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Analytics 10: Raw Logs — page 1, limit 10
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}/logs?page=1&limit=10
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Analytics 11: Raw Logs — page 2
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}/logs?page=2&limit=10
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Analytics 12: Raw Logs — limit capped at 200 (request 9999, expect ≤200 returned)
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}/logs?limit=9999
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Analytics 13: Cross-user 403 — use tokenB to access projectA (expect 403)
# @name crossUserCheck
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}/analytics/summary
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.accessToken}}
